FBIS3-17276 "drsov057_b_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Witnesses Claim Mid-Air Explosion LD2303140394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1327 GMT 23 Mar 94 LD2303140394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Manvelov] [Excerpts] Moscow, 23 Mar -- Rescue teams are carrying out an on-the-spot investigation of the burnt-out debris of the Aeroflot Airbus A-310-300 which crashed last night near Mezhdurechensk in Kuzbass and measures are being taken to find out what caused the airliner, regarded as one of the world's safest planes, to crash. [passage omitted] Representatives of the Russian airlines' ground services state that no technical malfunction was registered on board the airliner prior to its flight. This is the reason why foreign news agencies speak of an act of subversion on board the plane. Some local residents, who saw and heard a mid-air explosion, are also of the same view. [passage omitted]
